General Wrap Program
------------------------------
Name: Jingcong Zhang         |
Email: jingcoz@g.clemson.edu |
Date: 2016-10-09             |
------------------------------
This program is to wrap an input image and optionally write out to an image file.

Run wrap to wrap image.
  The program provide two types of wrap operation:
    mode 1 - stretch image: magnify the right side and minify the left side
    mode 2 - twirl image: increase the wrap parameter to enhance image twirling
  The default mode is twirl image with wrap parameter 2.
  -Usage: 
    wrap input_image_name [output_image_name] [mode] [wrap_parameter]
  -Mouse Response:
    Left click any of the displayed windows to quit the program.

Run tile to tile image with a number of horizontal and vertical repetitions.
  Input image and output image will keep the same size.
  -Usage: 
    tile row_number column_number input_image_name [output_image_name]
  -Mouse Response:
    Left click any of the displayed windows to quit the program.
